    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Regional style of temple architecture of 11th/13th-century Kalinga, which was a territorial subdivision of east-central India, corresponding to present-day northern Andhra Pradesh, most of Orissa, and a portion of Madhya Pradesh states.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
